article.headline: Bowling Green 55, Miami (Ohio) 52
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Nate Miller and Darryl Clements each scored 15 points to lead Bowling Green to a 55-52 win over Miami of Ohio on Wednesday night. Ahead 53-52 with 25 seconds left, Chris Knight made a jumper to push the Falcons' lead to three. Miami inbounded the ball with six seconds remaining, but Kenny Hayes missed a 3-point attempt as time expired. Knight finished with 11 points and nine rebounds for Bowling Green (8-9, 3-2 Mid-American). Tim Pollitz led the RedHawks (7-10, 1-4) with 15 points. Alex Moosmann added 11 and Hayes had 10. The Falcons shot 45.5 percent from the field (20 of 44) while Miami shot 39 percent (20 of 51).
